erns\n  78→- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n  79→- F-009: high-risk command keywords trigger confirmation flow (rm -rf, sudo, etc.)\n  80→- F-009: blacklist commands are rejected before execution\n  81→- F-009: long output is paginated with /more for remaining pages\n  82→- F-010: file operations restricted to TELEGRAM_FILE_ALLOWED_ROOTS (defaults: cwd, Desktop, Downloads, tmpdir)\n  83→- F-010: file download limited to 50MB for documents, 10MB for images\n  84→- F-010: binary files cannot be displayed as text\n  85→- F-011: AI CLI process tracked per session, can be interrupted via /stop\n  86→- F-011: AI CLI heartbeat notifications configurable via AI_CLI_HEARTBEAT_THRESHOLD_MS/INTERVAL_MS\n  87→- F-012: /kill requires admin role and confirmation before terminating process\n  88→- F-012: alert rules stored in data/alert-rules.json, persisted across restarts\n  89→- F-012: alert cooldown prevents notification spam (5 min default)\n  90→- F-013: sessions keyed by telegram chat ID (sessionKey = \"telegram:<chatId>\")\n  91→- F-013: session timeout defaults to 30 min, configurable via SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS\n  92→- F-013: /history shows recent commands (default 10), max 100\n  93→- F-013: /alias requires operator role, per-user storage\n  94→- F-013: /sessions requires admin role, shows all active sessions\n  95→- F-013: aliases stored in data/aliases.json, persisted immediately\n  96→- F-013: session context persisted to data/sessions/ directory\n  97→\n  98→DECISIONS:\n  99→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n 100→- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n 101→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n 102→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for featu