{"type":"assistant","uuid":"2026031305211636c48dc6edf04e3a","session_id":"34f919b8-df8c-46e5-a3ef-c48e25e357c2","message":{"id":"2026031305211636c48dc6edf04e3a","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_2e1c6aa38dae416abb11593b","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-013: Session and Context Manager — Context Snapshot\n\n**Feature ID**: F-013\n**Session**: F-013-20260313051900\n**Created**: 2026-03-13\n\n---\n\n## Section 1 — Feature Brief\n\n### Description\n\n会话管理与上下文保持系统，为多用户场景提供独立的会话隔离和状态管理。每个 Telegram 用户有独立的工作上下文（当前工作目录、环境变量覆盖、命令历史），会话超时后自动清理。\n\n### Core Capabilities\n\n- **多用户会话隔离**: 每个用户的工作目录、环境变量互不干扰\n- **命令历史**: /history 查看近期执行的命令，支持 /history N 指定条数\n- **命令别名**: /alias name=command 定义常用命令快捷方式，/alias 查看所有别名，别名持久化存储\n- **会话超时**: 配置 SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS 后不活跃会话自动清理并通知用户\n- **管理员能力**: admin 用户可通过 /sessions 查看所有活跃会话\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. 每个用户有独立的会话上下文，工作目录和环境变量互不干扰\n2. /history 可查看近期命令历史，支持指定条数\n3. /alias 支持定义、查看和删除命令别名，别名持久化存储\n4. 会话超时后自动清理临时状态并通知用户\n5. 管理员可通过 /sessions 查看所有活跃会话的概要信息\n6. 会话状态在 Bot 重启后可从持久化存储恢复\n\n### Dependencies\n\n- F-009 - General Command Executor (completed): provides session cwd, output pagination, /cd /more commands\n- F-006 - Safety and Permission Guard (completed): provides permission tiers (viewer, operator, admin)\n\n---\n\n## Section 2 — Project Structure\n\n```\nsrc/\n├── config.js                     # Configuration with F-013 settings\n├── services/\n│   ├── index.js                  # Service exports\n│   ├── session-store.js          # In-memory session state (extended for F-013)\n│   ├── session-context-service.js # Session lifecycle & persistence (F-013)\n│   ├── alias-store.js            # Alias persistence (F-013)\n│   └── command-executor-service.js # Records commands to history (F-009/F-013)\n├── bot/\n│   ├── telegram.js               # Bot initialization, registers F-013 commands\n│   └── commands/\n│       ├── index.js              # Command registration & routing\n│       ├── registry.js           # Command registry\n│       └── handlers/\n│           ├── history.js        # /history command (F-013)\n│           ├── alias.js          # /alias command (F-013)\n│           └── sessions.js       # /sessions command (F-013)\ntests/\n├── services/\n│   ├── session-store-f013.test.js\n│   ├── session-context-service.test.js\n│   └── alias-store.test.js\n└── bot/commands/handlers/\n    ├── history.test.js\n    ├── alias.test.js\n    └── sessions.test.js\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 3 — Prizm Context\n\n### From root.prizm (L0)\n\n```\nDOC_LEVEL: L0\nPROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\nPROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\nPLATFORM: codebuddy\nLANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\nPACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\nENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n```\n\n### From runtime.prizm (L1) — F-013 Relevant TRAPS\n\n```\nTRAPS:\n- F-013: sessions keyed by telegram chat ID (sessionKey = \"telegram:<chatId>\")\n- F-013: session timeout defaults to 30 min, configurable via SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS\n- F-013: /history shows recent commands (default 10), max 100\n- F-013: /alias requires operator role, per-user storage\n- F-013: /sessions requires admin role, shows all active sessions\n- F-013: aliases stored in data/aliases.json, persisted immediately\n- F-013: session context persisted to data/sessions/ directory\n```\n\n### Configuration (from src/config.js)\n\n```javascript\n// F-013: Session and Context Manager\nSESSION_TIMEOUT_MS: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(1800000), // 30 min\nSESSION_HISTORY_MAX: z.coerce.number().int().positive().default(100),\nSESSION_PERSISTENCE_DIR: z.string().optional().default('data/sessions'),\nALIAS_PERSISTENCE_PATH: z.string().optional().default('data/aliases.json')\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 4 — Existing Source Files\n\n### src/services/session-store.js (F-013 Extensions)\n\n```javascript\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\n\nclass SessionStore {\n  #messagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #commitsBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-009: Command executor extensions\n  #cwdBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #outputPagesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-010: File search results state for pagination\n  #searchResultsBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-011: AI CLI process tracking\n  #activeProcessBySessionKey = new Map();\n  // F-013: Session and Context Manager\n  #commandHistoryBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #envOverridesBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #lastActivityBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #userIdBySessionKey = new Map();\n  #sessionCreatedAtBySessionKey = new Map();\n\n  // ... existing methods for messages, commits, cwd, output pages, search results, active process ...\n\n  // F-013: Session and Context Manager methods\n\n  recordCommand(sessionKey, command, exitCode) { /* ... */ }\n  getCommandHistory(sessionKey, limit) { /* ... */ }\n  setEnvOverride(sessionKey, key, value) { /* ... */ }\n  getEnvOverrides(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  touchSession(sessionKey, userId) { /* ... */ }\n  getLastActivity(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  getSessionInfo(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  getAllSessionKeys() { /* ... */ }\n  getSessionAge(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  getIdleTime(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  setUserId(sessionKey, userId) { /* ... */ }\n  getUserId(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n\n  // clear() extended to clear F-013 data\n}\n\nexport const sessionStore = new SessionStore();\n```\n\n### src/services/session-context-service.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { mkdir, readFile, writeFile, unlink, readdir } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { join } from 'node:path';\nimport { config } from '../config.js';\nimport { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n\nclass SessionContextServiceClass {\n  #dataDir = null;\n  #notificationCallback = null;\n  #timeoutWatcherId = null;\n  #isInitialized = false;\n  #timeoutMs = null;\n  #checkIntervalMs = null;\n\n  reset() { /* ... */ }\n  isInitialized() { /* ... */ }\n  initSessionContext({ dataDir, timeoutMs, checkIntervalMs }) { /* ... */ }\n  createSession(sessionKey, userId) { /* ... */ }\n  getOrCreateSession(sessionKey, userId) { /* ... */ }\n  touchSession(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  cleanupSession(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  persistSession(sessionKey) { /* ... */ }\n  restoreSessions() { /* ... */ }\n  startTimeoutWatcher() { /* ... */ }\n  stopTimeoutWatcher() { /* ... */ }\n  isWatcherRunning() { /* ... */ }\n  setNotificationCallback(callback) { /* ... */ }\n}\n\nexport const sessionContextService = new SessionContextServiceClass();\n```\n\n### src/services/alias-store.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { mkdir, readFile, writeFile } from 'node:fs/promises';\nimport { dirname } from 'node:path';\n\nclass AliasStoreClass {\n  #persistencePath = null;\n  #aliases = new Map(); // Map<userId, Map<aliasName, command>>\n  #isInitialized = false;\n\n  reset() { /* ... */ }\n  isInitialized() { /* ... */ }\n  initAliasStore({ persistencePath }) { /* ... */ }\n  loadAliases() { /* ... */ }\n  saveAliases() { /* ... */ }\n  setAlias(userId, name, command) { /* ... */ }\n  getAlias(userId, name) { /* ... */ }\n  getAllAliases(userId) { /* ... */ }\n  deleteAlias(userId, name) { /* ... */ }\n  resolveAlias(userId, name) { /* ... */ }\n  clear() { /* ... */ }\n}\n\nexport const aliasStore = new AliasStoreClass();\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/handlers/history.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { sessionStore } from '../../../services/session-store.js';\n\nexport const historyMeta = {\n  name: 'history',\n  aliases: ['h'],\n  description: '查看命令执行历史',\n  usage: '/history [N]',\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'viewer',\n  helpText: '/history [N] - 查看最近执行的命令历史'\n};\n\nexport async function handleHistory(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply, sessionId, args = [] } = handlerCtx;\n  // Parse count, get history, format and send\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/handlers/alias.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { aliasStore } from '../../../services/alias-store.js';\n\nexport const aliasMeta = {\n  name: 'alias',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '管理命令别名',\n  usage: '/alias [name=command] 或 /alias del <name>',\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'operator',\n  helpText: '/alias - 查看别名列表；/alias name=command - 定义别名；/alias del name - 删除别名'\n};\n\nexport async function handleAlias(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply, userId, args = [] } = handlerCtx;\n  // No args: list all; 'del' subcommand: delete; else: define\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/commands/handlers/sessions.js\n\n```javascript\nimport { sessionStore } from '../../../services/session-store.js';\n\nexport const sessionsMeta = {\n  name: 'sessions',\n  aliases: [],\n  description: '查看所有活跃会话（仅管理员）',\n  usage: '/sessions',\n  requiresAuth: true,\n  minRole: 'admin',\n  helpText: '/sessions - 查看所有活跃会话的概要信息（仅管理员）'\n};\n\nexport async function handleSessions(handlerCtx) {\n  const { reply } = handlerCtx;\n  // Get all session keys, build formatted list\n}\n```\n\n### src/bot/telegram.js (F-013 Integration)\n\n```javascript\n// F-013: Initialize session context service\nawait sessionContextService.initSessionContext({ dataDir: config.sessionPersistenceDir });\nawait aliasStore.initAliasStore({ persistencePath: config.aliasPersistencePath });\n\n// F-013: Restore sessions from disk\nawait sessionContextService.restoreSessions();\n\n// F-013: Set up notification callback for session timeout\nsessionContextService.setNotificationCallback(async (sessionKey, userId) => {\n  const chatId = sessionKey.replace('telegram:', '');\n  await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, '⏰ 会话因长时间未活动已超时，相关状态已清理。');\n});\n\n// F-013: Start timeout watcher\nsessionContextService.startTimeoutWatcher();\n\n// F-013: Register commands\nregisterCommand(historyMeta, handleHistory);\nregisterCommand(aliasMeta, handleAlias);\nregisterCommand(sessionsMeta, handleSessions);\n```\n\n---\n\n## Section 5 — Existing Tests\n\nAll F-013 tests pass:\n\n- `tests/services/session-store-f013.test.js`: Tests for command history, env overrides, activity tracking, session metadata\n- `tests/services/session-context-service.test.js`: Tests for session lifecycle, persistence, timeout watcher\n- `tests/services/alias-store.test.js`: Tests for alias CRUD, persistence, user isolation\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/history.test.js`: Tests for /history command\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/alias.test.js`: Tests for /alias command\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/sessions.test.js`: Tests for /sessions command\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Status\n\n**COMPLETE** — All acceptance criteria are satisfied:\n\n1. ✅ Each user has independent session context (sessionStore isolation by sessionKey)\n2. ✅ /history shows command history with count support\n3. ✅ /alias supports define/view/delete with persistence\n4. ✅ Session timeout cleanup with notification callback\n5. ✅ Admin can view all active sessions via /sessions\n6. ✅ Session state persists to data/sessions/ and restores on startup\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/013-session-and-context-manager/context-snapshot.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":86196,"output_tokens":2914,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:22:07.948Z","_requestId":"47d23dc854de4b359e56f15c300d9539"}
