{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260313052208bb2bb5fa39e14d94","session_id":"34f919b8-df8c-46e5-a3ef-c48e25e357c2","message":{"id":"20260313052208bb2bb5fa39e14d94","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_9e72616343b14dafa65610c7","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-013: Session and Context Manager — Implementation Plan\n\n**Feature ID**: F-013\n**Status**: COMPLETE\n**Created**: 2026-03-13\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Telegram Bot                             │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐              │\n│  │ /history    │  │ /alias      │  │ /sessions   │              │\n│  │ handler     │  │ handler     │  │ handler     │              │\n│  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘              │\n└─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼─────────────────────┘\n          │                │                │\n          ▼                ▼                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Service Layer                             │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐   │\n│  │         sessionStore               │  │    aliasStore    │   │\n│  │  - In-memory session state         │  │  - User aliases  │   │\n│  │  - Command history                 │  │  - Persistence   │   │\n│  │  - Env overrides                   │  │                  │   │\n│  │  - Activity tracking               │  │                  │   │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘   │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │              sessionContextService                          │ │\n│  │  - Session lifecycle management                             │ │\n│  │  - Persistence to data/sessions/                            │ │\n│  │  - Timeout watcher with notifications                       │ │\n│  │  - Restore on startup                                       │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n          │\n          ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       Persistence Layer                          │\n│  ┌──────────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │ data/sessions/       │  │ data/aliases.json            │     │\n│  │ telegram_<id>.json   │  │ { userId: { name: cmd } }    │     │\n│  └──────────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────────┘     │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Data Flow\n\n```\nUser sends command\n        │\n        ▼\n┌───────────────────┐\n│ Permission Guard  │  Check minRole requirement\n└────────┬──────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌───────────────────┐\n│ Command Handler   │  /history, /alias, /sessions\n└────────┬──────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌───────────────────┐\n│ Service Layer     │  sessionStore / aliasStore / sessionContextService\n└────────┬──────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌───────────────────┐\n│ Reply to User     │  Formatted message\n└───────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Timeout Flow\n\n```\nsessionContextService.startTimeoutWatcher()\n        │\n        ▼\n┌───────────────────┐\n│ Interval Timer    │  Every 60 seconds (default)\n└────────┬──────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌───────────────────┐\n│ Check All Sessions│  sessionStore.getAllSessionKeys()\n└────────┬──────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌───────────────────┐\n│ Get Idle Time     │  sessionStore.getIdleTime()\n└────────┬──────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n    idleTime > timeoutMs?\n         │\n    ┌────┴────┐\n    │ Yes     │ No\n    ▼         ▼\n┌─────────┐  (skip)\n│ cleanup │\n│ Session │\n└────┬────┘\n     │\n     ▼\n┌───────────────────┐\n│ Notify User       │  notificationCallback\n└───────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n### Created Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/services/session-context-service.js` | Session lifecycle, persistence, timeout |\n| `src/services/alias-store.js` | Alias persistence and resolution |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/history.js` | /history command |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/alias.js` | /alias command |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/sessions.js` | /sessions command |\n\n### Modified Files\n\n| File | Changes |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/services/session-store.js` | Added F-013 data maps and methods |\n| `src/services/index.js` | Export new services |\n| `src/config.js` | Added SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS, SESSION_HISTORY_MAX, SESSION_PERSISTENCE_DIR, ALIAS_PERSISTENCE_PATH |\n| `src/bot/telegram.js` | Initialize services, restore sessions, start watcher, register commands |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n- `tests/services/session-store-f013.test.js`: SessionStore extensions\n- `tests/services/session-context-service.test.js`: Session lifecycle\n- `tests/services/alias-store.test.js`: Alias CRUD and persistence\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/history.test.js`: /history command\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/alias.test.js`: /alias command\n- `tests/bot/commands/handlers/sessions.test.js`: /sessions command\n\n### Integration Points\n\n- F-009: Command executor calls `sessionStore.recordCommand()` after execution\n- F-006: Permission guard enforces minRole for /alias (operator) and /sessions (admin)\n\n---\n\n## Configuration\n\n| Env Variable | Default | Description |\n|-------------|---------|-------------|\n| `SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS` | 1800000 (30 min) | Session inactivity timeout |\n| `SESSION_HISTORY_MAX` | 100 | Max commands stored per session |\n| `SESSION_PERSISTENCE_DIR` | data/sessions | Directory for session files |\n| `ALIAS_PERSISTENCE_PATH` | data/aliases.json | File for alias storage |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Permission Levels**:\n   - `/history`: viewer (lowest, any authenticated user)\n   - `/alias`: operator (requires elevated privilege)\n   - `/sessions`: admin (highest privilege)\n\n2. **User Isolation**:\n   - Aliases are per-user (keyed by Telegram user ID)\n   - Session data is per-user (keyed by Telegram chat ID)\n   - No cross-user data access\n\n3. **Persistence Security**:\n   - Session files stored in `data/sessions/` with sanitized names\n   - Alias file stored as `data/aliases.json`\n   - Both should be in `.gitignore` for production\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Mapping\n\n| Criteria | Implementation |\n|----------|---------------|\n| Independent session context | `sessionStore` uses sessionKey = \"telegram:<chatId>\" |\n| /history with count support | `handleHistory()` parses args, caps at 100 |\n| /alias define/view/delete | `handleAlias()` handles all three modes |\n| Session timeout cleanup | `sessionContextService.#checkTimeouts()` |\n| Admin /sessions view | `handleSessions()` with minRole: admin |\n| Persistence across restarts | `persistSession()`, `restoreSessions()` |\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/013-session-and-context-manager/plan.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":89154,"output_tokens":1805,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"__timestamp":"2026-03-12T21:22:41.226Z","_requestId":"47d23dc854de4b359e56f15c300d9539"}
